##prepare senate matrix for rollcall object

senateNames <- df_senate[,1]
senateData <- matrix(df_senate[ , 2], length(df_senate[ , 2]), 1)
colnames(senateData) <- "party"
df_senate <- df_senate[, -c(1,2)]
##generate wnominate senate scores

rc_senate <- rollcall(df_senate, yea=1, nay=2, missing=4, notInLegis=3,
               legis.names=senateNames, legis.data=senateData)

result_senate <- wnominate(rc_senate, polarity=1, dims=1)

##import census data
##read RUCA data

house_urzip = read.csv("house_urzip.csv")
senate_urzip = read.csv("senate_urzip.csv")
##add wnominate scores to RUCA object

house_urzip$conserve_house <- result_house$legislators$coord1D

senate_urzip$conserve_senate <- result_senate$legislators$coord1D
##prepare regression models

fit_house <- lm(conserve_house ~ Educational.Attainment + Male.Population + Poverty.Line + RUCA1 + White.Population, house_urzip)

fit_senate <- lm(conserve_senate ~ Educational.Attainment + Male.Population + Poverty.Line + RUCA1 + White.Population, senate_urzip)
##run regression models

library(stargazer)

stargazer(fit_house, type="text")

##export RUCA and wnominate data for leaflet creation later

write.csv(house_urzip, "house_merge_urzip.csv", row.names = FALSE)

write.csv(senate_urzip, "senate_merge_urzip.csv", row.names = FALSE)
##read shapefiles

map_house <- shapefile("ok_house_2020.shp")
map_senate <- shapefile("ok_senate_2020.shp")
##merge wnominate&RUCA data with shapefiles

house_merge <- geo_join(map_house, house_urzip, "district", "House.District")
## Warning: We recommend using the dplyr::*_join() family of functions instead.
senate_merge <- geo_join(map_senate, senate_urzip, "district", "Senate.District")
## Warning: We recommend using the dplyr::*_join() family of functions instead.
##create house choropleth

palette.house <- brewer.pal(n = 9, name = "RdBu")


spplot(house_merge, "conserve_house", main = "Partisan Score by House District", col.regions = rev(palette.house), cuts = 8, col = "black")

##create senate choropleth

palette.senate <- brewer.pal(n = 9, name = "RdBu")


spplot(senate_merge, "conserve_senate", main = "Partisan Score by Senate District", col.regions = rev(palette.senate), cuts = 8, col = "black")
